    {
      "id": "1944750c-f3ba-80f7-b8b9-c06b43acf33b",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Putting students into the correct groups is one of the most challenging tasks. Authors explore an approach to create heterogenous groups that have inter-group homogeneity. The approach assumes that there is a hierarchy to the characteristics the professor wants to use for grouping. Authors use this hierarchy to transform the hierarchy into a lexicographic optimization problem.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1944750c-f3ba-80f7-b8b9-c06b43acf33b",
        "parent": {
